This article discusses the enhanced cooperation between the United States and China on climate change, clean energy, and the environment. The leaders of both countries have agreed to collaborate on the development and deployment of clean energy technologies, with the aim of stimulating economic growth and job creation. They are committed to implementing the provisions of the Cancun Agreements and working together to address climate change through various forums, including the U.N. Framework Convention on Climate Change and the U.S.-China Climate Policy Dialogue. The article also mentions the joint work plans under the U.S.-China Clean Energy Research Center, the new initiatives under the Ten Year Framework for Cooperation on Energy and Environment, and the signing of various memoranda of understanding and agreements to promote cooperation in energy sciences, electric vehicle demonstrations, and eco-city development.